## Stage 1 — UNDERSTAND

**Contract (R2):**
- set/get round-trips int and str values; get of never-set cell is None
- set accepts str starting with "=" without error (stored as formula; phase 2 evaluates)
- bool raw raises ValueError; float, None, list raws raise ValueError
- int-subclass and str-subclass instances accepted and normalized: type(get(...)) is exactly int or str
- set returns None on success; set on occupied cell replaces content
- set that raises ValueError leaves prior content and eval_count unchanged
- eval_count stays 0 across literal set/get calls

## Stage 2 — PLAN

**Files to modify:**
- `gridcalc/sheet.py` — extend set/get with type validation and normalization
- `tests/test_store.py` — new test file for literal value storage

**Approach:** Extend existing Sheet class with stricter type checking in set(), normalize subclasses to plain types.

